text: Vennesla Church () is the main parish church in Vennesla municipality in Agder county, Norway. It is located in the village of Vennesla. The church serves the Vennesla parish in the Otredal deanery in the Diocese of Agder og Telemark. The church is also the seat of the dean of the Otredal deanery. The white, stone and wood church was completed in October 1829 and it was consecrated on 22 August 1830. The church seats about 240 people. ==See also== *List of churches in Vest-Agder ==References== Category:Churches in Agder Category:Vennesla Category:19th-century Church of Norway church buildings
